@18 = ~These enchanted girdles started appearing shortly after the end of the Time of Troubles.  Priests of Mystra took it to be a sign that their goddess had returned to power, while others saw it as a sign that the gods desired to take a more active role in the Realms from now on.  Exactly how many of these exist is not known, but there are thought to be at least a dozen around.

Each girdle is bonded to a particular god, although any priest who shares the same moral alignment as the deity may use a belt, they need not be a follower.  This particular girdle has a symbol of the rising sun, marking it as bonded to the Morning Lord, Lathander.

STATISTICS:

